<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="143" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,403,1978]" box="[151,1226,403,430]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,403,429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Description.</emphasis>
Female. Body medium. Face ovoid, with impressed dots (
<figureCitation box="[950,1039,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,882,906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in ventral view; F. seventh abdominal sternite and subgenital plate in ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Ocelli distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,403,1978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fore coxae with 1 small spine. Fore and middle tibiae ventrally with 4 pairs of spurs and 1 pair of apical spurs; middle tibiae with one internal spine on dorsal surface. Hind femora with 11 internal and 8–11 external spines on ventral surface, dorsal surface of tibiae with 6 pairs of spines, ventral surface with 1 pair of subapical spines, apices with 1 pair of dorsal spurs and 2 pairs of ventral spurs.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,403,1978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
Wings just reaching the apex of abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[702,827,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-78@2.[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A–B. habitus in lateral view; C–D. tegmina in dorsal view: C. left tegmen, D. right tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702227/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). Tegmina: Radius with two branches R and RS, both forked near tip or not. Media of left tegmen divides before mid-length of tegmen into two veins, MA and MP; cubitus anterior undivided, free throughout (
<figureCitation box="[629,719,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-78@2.[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A–B. habitus in lateral view; C–D. tegmina in dorsal view: C. left tegmen, D. right tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702227/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). While media anterior of right tegmen single-branched, media posterior absent, cubitus anterior forks about mid-length of tegmen into two veins, CuA1 and CuA2 (
<figureCitation box="[1273,1363,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-78@2.[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A–B. habitus in lateral view; C–D. tegmina in dorsal view: C. left tegmen, D. right tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702227/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Both tegmina: cubitus posterior undivided, free throughout; with 3 anal veins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,403,1978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
Second and third abdominal tergites each with two rows of stridulatory pegs (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1194,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,882,906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in ventral view; F. seventh abdominal sternite and subgenital plate in ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Seventh abdominal sternite longer than wide, lateral margins widening, posterior margin arched; ventral surface with one sclerotized transverse fold (
<figureCitation box="[332,416,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,882,906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in ventral view; F. seventh abdominal sternite and subgenital plate in ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate transverse with a pair of tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1102,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,882,906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in ventral view; F. seventh abdominal sternite and subgenital plate in ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor short, apart from sub-basal gradually and obliquely curved upward, apical area slightly curved dorsad, apices obtuse; basal area of ventro valvulae with 1 pair of lobate processes, its apices widely arched.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,403,1978]" box="[199,392,943,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,943,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,403,1978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,979,1005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Coloration.</emphasis>
General color yellow brown (
<figureCitation box="[675,800,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-78@2.[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A–B. habitus in lateral view; C–D. tegmina in dorsal view: C. left tegmen, D. right tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702227/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). Eyes black; ocelli pale (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1179,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,882,906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in ventral view; F. seventh abdominal sternite and subgenital plate in ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with black margins, which widened at anterior and posterior margins (
<figureCitation box="[815,902,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,882,906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,179,856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. dorsal view, C. lateral view; D. second and third abdominal tergites in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in ventral view; F. seventh abdominal sternite and subgenital plate in ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface of abdomen with black central area. Tegmina yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[519,643,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1555,1579]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-78@2.[151,1436,990,1535]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Metriogryllacris (Metriogryllacris) nigrilimbis Liu &amp; Bian sp. nov. Female: A–B. habitus in lateral view; C–D. tegmina in dorsal view: C. left tegmen, D. right tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702227/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Fig. 2C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,403,1978]" box="[199,1275,1087,1114]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,453,1087,1113]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Body 20.6; pronotum 5.2; tegmina 15.9; hind femur 11.1; ovipositor 7.4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
